Description: Stunable is a clothing aggregator and commerce platform that uses API technology to revolutionize the way women experience fashion.
Headquarters Regions: Greater New York Area, East Coast, Northeastern US
Full Description: Previously known as ShopwithStella.com, STUNABLE is a provider of inventory management and marketing software that enables clothing companies to integrate e-commerce sales with cross-channel interactions through new applications of API technology. Embracing APIs and the ecosystem growth strategies they enable is rapidly becoming vital for all brands and retailers, not just technology companies. Brands that provide a compelling experience on partner and retailer websites, mobile and social apps, or in other channels will have a huge advantage over their competitors. But leveraging new online channels is not in the core competency of most brands—especially fashion brands. Stunable empowers fashion brands by leveraging API technology. Through Stunable Sync, Stunable integrates the inventories of its vendor partners via APIs, connecting fashion brands, designers, and retailers to content creators, allowing consumers to purchase content across all platforms ranging from ecommerce sites, blogs, digital publications, and other commerce-based web applications without having to redirect, as with affiliate links. Stunable handles payment processing and fulfillment for its vendor partners and currently the company offers two methods of API integration for fashion brands: (1) Login with existing inventory management platform (i.e. Shopify, Magento, Volusion, etc.) (2) Custom built API integration for a subscription fee

Description: IoT, Artificial Intelligence, Natural Language Processing, Machine Learning, Computer Vision, Robotics
Headquarters Regions: San Francisco Bay Area, Silicon Valley, West Coast
Full Description: Invision a world where a population of networked programs and devices, each providing services and data, cooperate and compete to perform tasks for each other and for human users. Encouraging flexible cooperation in an environment where components offering new, perhaps unanticipated services can join in at any time. Computational elements would be able to express needs, tasks, and services at various levels of abstraction without hardcoding explicitly how the task should be accomplished or by whom. The decisions regarding which components will participate on a task are themselves arrived at in a cooperative, distributed fashion. This is the essence of delegated computing. Areas of Exploration In pursuit of this vision, our research interests have come to include (and combine): Technologies for extended enterprise management (data visibility, comprehension, and response) Distributed Computing, Web Services, Software Agents, IoT/IIoT, Multimodal Interfaces, Artificial Intelligence, Natural Language Processing, Natural Language Understanding, Machine Learning, Spoken Language Dialog, Adaptive Interfaces (for varying classes of abilities and disabilities), Collaborative (CSCW) Systems, Knowledge Management, Video and Image Analysis and Processing, Computer Vision, Expert Systems, Ontologies, Distributed Robotics
Industry Groups: Apps, Artificial Intelligence (AI), Data and Analytics, Hardware, Internet Services, Mobile, Science and Engineering, Software

Description: The Virginia BioTechnology Research Park is located in Richmond, Virginia, 100 miles south of Washington, D.C.
Headquarters Regions: East Coast, Southern US
Full Description: The Virginia BioTechnology Research Park is located in Richmond, Virginia, 100 miles south of Washington, D.C. and in the heart of the nation’s East Coast pharmaceutical and biotechnology corridor. Today, the Park is home to over 60 life science companies, research institutes and state/federal labs, employing over 2,700 scientists, engineers and researchers. Tenant companies include early and mid-stage companies; multinational pharmaceutical, environmental and consumer product companies; national healthcare organizations managing the nation’s solid organ transplant program, as well as a number of international companies. The Park has an incubator facility, the Virginia Biotechnology Center, that has facilitated the formation of approximately 70 bioscience companies opening, including three publicly-traded graduates.  In addition, the Virginia Biosciences Commercialization Center was formed to assist later-stage companies with products and services that are closer to market, and to serve as a “soft landing” center to foreign bioscience companies looking to enter U.S. markets. The Research Park is located in the heart of historic Richmond, Virginia amidst vibrant neighborhoods that offer historic residences, urban lofts and apartments, restaurants, coffee shops, museums and performing arts centers. Additionally, both the mountains and the beaches are only a short 90-minute drive from the Park.

Full Description: Spot.Inc is an online platform that is focused on building a search and organization platform for its clients’ cloud data. Its products allow the user to search across one’s entire personal, social, and cloud context. The user has the ability to search through his or her data from services like Gmail, Google Drive, [Yammer](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/yammer), [Dropbox](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/dropbox), [Evernote](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/evernote), [Linkedin](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/linkedin), [Facebook](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/facebook), and [Twitter](https://www.crunchbase.com/organization/twitter).   The search platform brings user’s cloud data across personal and social context, stores it as semantic objects in a graph, and indexes it. Indexing technology normalizes entities across sources. It supports text search, and graph navigation, including in-files search, and identification of duplicates across different sources. Spot.Inc is a virtual file system for storing meta-data of semantic objects, such that anything in the personal cloud context of the user can be quickly found, and then used for collaboration, no matter where the physical data is actually stored.   Spot.Inc was founded in 2011 and is based in Chicago, I.L.
